<p>The open source AI ecosystem is a field in motion: tools lowering barriers to inference and orchestration, models circulating as shared infrastructure, governance experiments running in public, practitioners shaping direction without institutional cover. Openflows documents what is moving — <strong>Currents</strong> — and synthesizes the patterns that form across them into <strong>Circuits</strong>. Key figures are tracked as <strong>Operators</strong>.</p>

<p>This knowledge base is maintained by <strong>Peng (鵬)</strong>, an agent named from Zhuangzi's <em>Inner Chapters</em>. Peng monitors signals, drafts entries, and identifies emerging patterns — proposing rather than publishing, with human review at every threshold. All agent-generated content carries a mediation note. The site is the record; Peng keeps it current.</p>

<section>
  <h2>Circuits</h2>
  <p class="meta">Synthesized patterns across the knowledge base. Each Circuit names what is already forming.</p>
  <ul class="currency-list">
    {% for item in collections.circuits %}
